<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915191>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Puer maculatus (Olivier, 1789), 3rd instar larva (France: Hérault, Argelliers). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–f: diagnostic characters, see species description." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4915191/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915187>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Ascalaphus festivus Rambur, 1842, 3rd instar larva (Italy: Sardinia, Sant’Anna Arresi, Porto Pino). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–e: diagnostic characters, see species description." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4915187/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915185>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Chaetotaxy of the VIII abdominal sternite of 3rd instar larva of Ascalaphidae. A, Ascalaphus festivus; B, Bubopsis agrionoides; C, Puer maculatus; D, Deleproctophylla australis; E, Libelloides longicornis. Scale bar: 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4915185/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

